  "conclusion": "With full-attention rowchunk2 fixed, grouped-compact MoE is generated-token-equality green for c5/c6/c7/c8 and first fails at the derived c9 boundary. Replacing only MoE with selected_c1 restores c9 equality at [137]*9. The post-c8 boundary is therefore a grouped-compact MoE row-count problem layered on top of the rowchunk2 full-attention diagnostic, not a rowchunk2 or linear-projection failure. No default extension or throughput claim is made. During final verification, one active c2 verify flaked red at [103,137] before the immediate final verify returned [137,137]; this is recorded separately and does not change the rowchunk2 MoE boundary conclusion, but it means c2 intermittent-flake risk remains open.",
